title: Frank Lloyd Wright Doormat—Coonley
description:
Make a good first impression with a punch of sophisticated color. Adapted from Frank Lloyd Wright's® (American, 1867-1959) design for the Avery Coonley Playhouse in Riverside, Illinois, c. 1912, our doormat is an architectural framework of durable rubber paired with natural handwoven and hand-painted coir fiber to welcome guests in style.   

30 x 18 in.

Additional Shipping $15 per Order.

This item cannot be shipped to a destination outside the United States.
